<br>
I am the blade of justice swung by the hand of war.<br>
<br>
I am rumbling death wrapped in metal with sharp pointy bits.<br>
<br>
I am Warrior.<br>
<br>
--<br>
<br>
On a less RP note...<br>
<br>
I have more days played on my warrior than I care to admit.<br>
<br>
I have seen all of EQ save Plane of Time.<br>
<br>
I can't seem to bring myself to play another class. I've made and deleted alts, I've played a necro, a ranger, two monks, two pallies, two SK's, three rogues, two wizards, a cleric, a shaman, and two bards over the course of three years yet I always come back to my warrior.<br>
<br>
Someone mentioned that one of the downsides to a warrior is no ports. Bah! This is one of the treasures of a warrior, we run everywhere. If a warrior is worth their salt, they know how to get anywhere. I've seen most of every zone I've been in, EQ is a huge game and being an explorer at heart I love seeing all of it.<br>
<br>
Warrior's are almost always in the fight, we are in the thick of the action in most fights. No sitting back and dozing for us, we fight.<br>
<br>
Sure they are downsides to a warrior, but for me, the upside is greater.<br>
<br>
