<br>
Warriors are fun though, and they are a very active class.  I punch as many buttons as your average bard during fights, and anybody that tells you playing a warrior is just standing there and hitting attack is a crappy warrior.  <br>
<br>
You should be able to tell from my sig that I consider warriors fun.  My current warrior is 49 after leveling to 65 and getting 45 AA points on my original warrior, and I'm having even more fun the 2nd time around (of course this time I'm twinked to the nines thanks to SW's favorite warlordess).  <br>
<br>
If you're going to get serious about playing a warrior, invest in a cobalt bracer, an incarnadine breastplate, gate potions of some sort (I use the thurgadin pottery ones), a fungi tunic, a snare weapon, and jboots or run 3.  Those items will make your life as a warrior much easier and more pleasant (although you can't use most of them until level 45).  <br>
<br>
